<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4736697>
        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "FIGURE 2. Symplectoscyphus cumberlandicus (Jäderholm, 1905): A, hydrothecae; B, gonotheca. Halecium exaggeratum Peña Cantero, Boero & Piraino, 2013: C, distal part of internode with hydrophore (arrow pointing to pseudodiaphragm) and hydrotheca. Schizotricha falcata Peña Cantero, 1998: D, forked hydrocladial internode and ahydrothecate internode (arrow); E, unforked hydrocladial internode showing hydrotheca and nematothecae; F, gonotheca; G–H, forked hydrocladial internodes from holotype (arrows pointing to perisarc indentations). Scale bar: 200 µm." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://zenodo.org/record/4736697/files/figure.png" .

